== 関連項目 == * {{prefix}} * {{intitle}}
{{DEFAULTSORT:かのえ}}
[[Category:干支]]

{{十干十二支}}
'''Kō''' (庚) is the seventh of the {{ill|Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}}.

In the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行説}} theory, it is associated with **yang metal (金の陽)**, which is why in Japan it is also called **"Kanoe" (金の兄, "Elder Metal")**.

== Overview ==  

* The kanji **庚** is a {{ill|pictogram|ja|象形文字}} representing a type of musical instrument.<ref>{{Citation| author=Ji Xusheng (季旭昇)| year=2014| title=説文新証| location=Taipei| publisher=芸文印書館| isbn=978-957-520-168-5| page=965}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Lin Zhiqiang et al. (林志強等)| year=2017| title=《文源》評注| location=Beijing| publisher=中国社会科学出版社| isbn=978-7-5203-0419-1| page=97}}</ref><ref>{{Citation| author=Ge Liang (葛亮)| year=2022| title=漢字再発現――従旧識到新知| location=Shanghai| publisher=上海書画出版社| isbn=978-7-5479-2884-4| pages=106–9}}</ref> The use of this character to represent the seventh stem is due to {{ill|phonetic loan|ja|仮借}}.
* In the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|西暦}} and the {{ill|Japanese Imperial Year|ja|神武天皇即位紀元}}, years ending in **0** (i.e., multiples of **10**) correspond to **Kō years (庚の年)**. Another name for such years is **Jōshō (上章)**.<ref>{{Cite web |title=古代天干地支的别称及解释_书法欣赏_词典网 |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08}}</ref>.
* In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|中国語の化合物命名法}}, **Kō (庚)** is used for **heptane (ヘプタン)**, **heptyl groups (ヘプチル基)**, and other compounds containing **seven carbon atoms**.
* According to the Five Elements' destructive cycle, **"Fire conquers Metal" (火剋金)**, meaning metal is subdued by fire. Thus, in traditional beliefs, days of **Kō during the peak fire season of summer** are considered inauspicious. These three Kō days in summer are called **Sanpuku (三伏)**.
* Its counterpart in the **Ten Stems polarity** is **Otsu (乙)**.
* **Eho (恵方, auspicious direction)** for **Kō years** is **west-southwest, slightly west (255°).**

== Earthly Branches containing Kō ==  
{{Wiktionary|庚}}  

* {{ill|Kōgo|ja|庚午}}  
* {{ill|Kōshin|ja|庚申}}  
* {{ill|Kōji|ja|庚子}}  
* {{ill|Kōin|ja|庚寅}}  
* {{ill|Kōshin|ja|庚辰}}  
* {{ill|Kōjutsu|ja|庚戌}}  

== References ==  
{{Reflist}}  

== See Also ==  
