* In the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Japanese Imperial Year|ja|神武天皇即位紀元|1=Japanese imperial year|qq=|12=draft}}, years ending in '''0''' (i.e., multiples of '''10''') correspond to '''Kō years (庚の年)'''. Another name for such years is '''Jōshō (上章)'''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=古代天干地支的别称及解释_书法欣赏_词典网 |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref>.
